      "writtenOn": "2019-09-27T20:41:52Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Once the deprecated onFilterBounds() and onFilterNodeBounds() functions go away, and onGetInputLayerBounds()\u0027s default implementation just calls visitInputLayerBounds(), we could simplify the code such that onGetInputLayerBounds() has this implementation, visit goes away, and subclasses that need to aggregate their children just call INHERITED::onGetInputLayerBounds() and pass in appropriate arguments. A similar approach could work for onGetOutputLayerBounds().\n\nFewer functions is nice, we still have an explicit call to perform aggregation in a subclass\u0027s bounds logic (also nice), but it\u0027s a little more magical in terms of knowing that the INHERITED function does that for you. A bridge to cross later, since they definitely have to be separate while juggling the old and new systems.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 446,
        "startChar": 46,
        "endLine": 446,
        "endChar": 67
      },
      "revId": "f636d92ea809cc82bcfe20c09716fd3146d5bb79",
