      "writtenOn": "2019-09-27T20:41:52Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t love having this bool for getting the input bounds w/o recursing to children. Unfortunately, this call in mapContext is a very legitimate use case for getting just this node\u0027s input bounds without recursing to the children.\n\nHowever, I really didn\u0027t like having two separate functions to control node-specific bounds and then node-aggregation logic and some filter types would override one but not the other, or both to be non-default for particular filtering directions. This argument is a lesser evil IMO.",
