      "side": 1,
      "message": "The downside to the template inversion compared to the earlier CL is that we now need a type-id to differentiate between Sk[I]Vector and Sk[I]Point.\n\nAnother way, that would avoid these SkDirection types, would be not use templates at all for the coordinate spaces and define SkLayerSpaceVector explicitly separately from SkLayerSpacePoint. The downside with that is that there is lots of redundant code for the device-space and parameter-space versions (or a weird inconsistency where they remain templates but the layer-space types are not).",
